  "prompt": "Which is a good refrence book for Servlets and JSP?",
  "response": "Here are some highly recommended reference books for Servlets and JSP:\n\n1. \"Head First Servlets and JSP\" by Bryan Basham, Kathy Sierra, and Bert Bates\n- Beginner-friendly\n- Highly visual and interactive approach\n- Covers fundamental concepts thoroughly\n\n2. \"Core Servlets and JavaServer Pages\" by Marty Hall and Larry Brown\n- Comprehensive coverage\n- Detailed explanations\n- Good for both beginners and intermediate developers\n\n3. \"Professional Java Server Programming\" by Jeff Heaton\n- In-depth technical details\n- Covers advanced server-side programming concepts\n- Includes practical examples\n\n4. \"Java Servlet Programming\" by Jason Hunter\n- Authoritative reference\n- Detailed technical explanation\n- Good for in-depth understanding\n\n5. \"JSP and Servlet Programming\" by Sue Spielman\n- Practical approach\n- Covers real-world scenarios\n- Good for hands-on learning\n\nOnline Resources:\n- Oracle's Official Documentation\n- Baeldung Tutorials\n- TutorialsPoint Servlets and JSP guides\n\nRecommendation: \"Head First Servlets and JSP\" for beginners, \"Core Servlets and JavaServer Pages\" for comprehensive learning.",
